article.headline: Second-half run keys San Antonio win
article.linkText: Silver Stars beat Lynx, end five-game skid
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- The Silver Stars got the second-half comeback
they've needed to end a five-game losing streak.

Marie Ferdinand scored 14 points in the second half and San
Antonio beat the Minnesota Lynx 78-71 on Tuesday night.

Katie Feenstra added 16 points, Wendy Palmer-Daniel and Shyra
Ely each had 11, and Shannon Johnson finished with 10 for the
Silver Stars, whose only other victory this month came July 2
against New York, 69-57.

Nicole Ohlde and Tamika Williams each scored 12 points, and
Vanessa Hayden finished with 10 points and 11 rebounds for
Minnesota. Amber Jacobs also scored 10 for the Lynx, who were going
for the 100th regular-season win in franchise history.

Minnesota's Katie Smith was limited to single-digit scoring for
the sixth time this season, finishing with five points -- well below
her 14-point average.

"It's a tough loss, you think your starters are going to step
it up and win it for you because they've done it in the past,"
Lynx head coach Suzie McConnell Serio said. "It hasn't been
happening. We need to go deeper into the bench."

LaToya Thomas returned to the lineup for San Antonio after
missing 13 games with a torn right labrum. She had two points in 6
minutes.

"We got a lot of energy from having LaToya Thomas back, and it
was pleasing to see the confidence we gained, especially
offensively," said Silver Stars coach Dan Hughes.

The Silver Stars trailed 37-30 at the break but opened the
second half with a 14-2 run. Ferdinand scored seven points in the
outburst.

Ferdinand, a three-time All-Star, missed her first five shots
but rebounded to finish 6-for-10 from the field.

San Antonio led by as many as 11 points before the Lynx rallied.
Ohlde completed Minnesota's comeback by tying the game with a pair
of free throws at the 3:52 mark.

The Silver Stars then scored eight straight points and sealed
the victory when Dalma Ivanyi hit a 3-pointer with 18 seconds left.
